    "narrative": "The headline for Ghost Ride the WHIP today is unequivocally **Corbin Carroll**, whose 87.14 efficiency score leads the roster by a wide margin. He draws a highly favorable matchup against Andrew Painter (xERA 4.82), and despite the slight penalty for an elite catcher, his position in the two-hole combined with high-upside park factors makes him our primary anchor. Elsewhere, **Gabriel Moreno** and **Mickey Moniak** provide excellent value today; **Gabriel Moreno** benefits from that same soft Painter matchup to yield a strong 70.57 score, while **Mickey Moniak** sees a massive 14% boost from a dynamic platoon advantage against Nick Pivetta, further amplified by favorable winds that project a strong outing.\n\nThe most difficult decision for today\u2019s lineup was between **Vinnie Pasquantino** and **Seiya Suzuki**. While **Vinnie Pasquantino** ultimately earned the utility spot with a 58.38 score\u2014largely due to his placement in the heart of the order and a positive wind profile\u2014**Seiya Suzuki** was the clear odd man out on the bench at 49.75. **Seiya Suzuki** actually projected well with the wind, but he was ultimately sunk by the unfavorable 3.09 xERA of the opposing starter and a lack of the high-leverage lineup placement that buoyed our starters. We are also keeping a close eye on the risk profiles for **James Wood** and **Vinnie Pasquantino**, both of whom are facing sub-3.00 xERA arms; they remain in the lineup for their situational utility, but their production will be heavily capped if they cannot navigate these elite pitchers efficiently. \n\nAs we continue to hunt for speed, **Brice Turang** remains a core tactical play. His 67.58 score is driven by his leadoff status and a +9% boost against Zack Littell\u2019s command profile. We are proceeding with caution regarding the \"Lineup Pending\" statuses for the entire roster; any shift in the batting order for **Trevor Story** or **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** could necessitate mid-day adjustments to our strategy. While **Zach McKinstry**, **Max Muncy**, and **Jose Caballero** remain on the bench as potential pivots, we are holding firm to preserve our games-played caps unless an injury or late scratch forces our hand.",
